  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But of the children of Israel did Solomon make no bondmen,.... For that was contrary to the law; they might be hired servants, but not bond servants, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 25:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but they were men of war; which he kept in pay, a standing army, maintained even in time of peace, in case of necessity, should an enemy attempt to invade or surprise them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and his servants; in his family and court, who had offices and employments there: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and his princes; ministers of state, counsellors, governors of cities, &c. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and his captains; officers in his army: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and rulers of his chariots and his horsemen; war chariots and troopers; see 1 Kings 9:19. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and rulers of his chariots and his horsemen; war chariots and troopers; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 9:19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
